elements.title: Dag Hammarskjöld Plaza
elements.contents: ... that actress Katharine Hepburn threatened to remove her name from a garden in Dag Hammarskjöld Plaza (pictured) when New York City officials said they would not widen the plaza?

elements.title: Maria Giustina Turcotti
elements.contents: ... that according to one critic, Italian opera singer Maria Giustina Turcotti "sang very well but was fat to the point of deformity"?

elements.title: 1824 US presidential election in Missouri
elements.contents: ... that the 1824 US presidential election in Missouri was not decided by the Electoral College, but by Missouri representative John Scott?

elements.title: Curtis Aiken
elements.contents: ... that Curtis Aiken set the New York State Public High School Athletic Association single-season boys' basketball scoring record?

elements.title: Baise Uprising
elements.contents: ... that Deng Xiaoping called his actions during the Baise Uprising "one of the worst mistakes" of his life?

elements.title: Asia Abdelmajid
elements.contents: ... that Asia Abdelmajid, a pioneering Sudanese actress, was killed in crossfire during the 2023 Sudan conflict?

elements.title: William Westerfeld
elements.contents: ... that confectioner William Westerfeld hired architect Henry Geilfuss to design his home in San Francisco, and then died in it?

elements.title: leopards
elements.contents: ... that the ancient Romans kept leopards in captivity to be used in the executions of criminals?
